SIMPLE: melancholy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melancholy
<hw>Mel"an*chol*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>melancolie</ets>, F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧lancolie</ets>, L.
<ets>melancholia</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/; <grk>me`las</grk>,
<grk>me`lanos</grk>, black + <?/ gall, bile. See <er>Malice</er>, and
1st <er>Gall</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Depression of spirits; a gloomy state continuing a
considerable time; deep dejection; gloominess.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Great and continued depression of spirits, amounting
to mental unsoundness; melancholia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Pensive meditation; serious thoughtfulness.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Hail, divinest <xex>Melancholy</xex> !⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Ill nature.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melancholy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Melancholy
<hw>Mel"an*chol*y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Depressed in
spirits; dejected; gloomy dismal.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Producing great evil and grief; causing dejection;
calamitous; afflictive; <as>as, a <ex>melancholy</ex>
event</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Somewhat deranged in mind; having the judgement
impaired.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Reynolds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Favorable to meditation; somber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A pretty, <qex>melancholy</qex> seat, well wooded and watered.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Gloomy; sad; dispirited; low-spirited;
downhearted; unhappy; hypochondriac; disconsolate; heavy, doleful;
dismal; calamitous; afflictive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melanconiaceae</ent>⟦br⟧
